history.text: Hey! Have you seen toy story?
No I have not, what is it about?
it has a 100% on rotten tomatoes
its an animated movie about toys
Oh wow that's a really good score. How old is it?

it came out in 1995 but is a cult classic and is not boring and still rele
vant
Interesting, have they ever released any sequels for it?
its about when people are away the toys come to life and go on adventures
i actually do not know if any sequels are out just that it is really popular
It sounds interesting. Does it have any famous voice over actors?
yes tom hanks plays woody and tim allen is buzz, don rickles is mr. potato head
these are just some of the characters there is ahuge famous cast
Very interesting. Do you know if it's a long movie or short movie?
i do not actually know the length of the movie just that it involves the toys and their owner andy
its about how a new toy buzz comes into their lives and takes the shine away from woody the main character
Okay well it definitely sounds very interesting. How are the quality of the digital effects?
it is apixar movie so they are very good plus it has a cinemascore of an A
Oh wow that's excellent. Does the movie have any draw backs in your opinion?
i would say if you are not into animated films watching the film may be something you hesitate on but the themes are very universal and it is enjoyable
definetely something you should give a chance

hmm okay. I thought the movie sounded a little childish but the voice actors makes me want to watch it. I wonder if the storyline is completely childish and cartoony. None the less, I'm interested in it.
it is really kid friendly but the overall concepts of being overshadowed and even being an outsiders makes it enjoyable
even jealousy is touche don
Interesting. So it sounds like it has some mature undertones in it. Does the movie take place indoors or outdoors primarily?
it really takes place in andy's room where the toys live but they do travel outside in certain scenes which makes the adventure part of the movie more interesting
its fun to watch them interact outside in the real world
Can you give one example of a place they travel to outside of the room?
they travel to a restaurant called pizza planet and they have to sneak into a car to do it, and you can imagine all the funny things that happen for that to happen
especially cause they do not want to get caught
That sounds interesting. Isn't there a character in it that can fly around?
so buzz the new character introduced has wings but actually cannot fly, he thinks he can but really can't
Ahh okay I see. Well it sounds really interesting and entertaining. I heard that Buzz, the character that thinks he can fly, is voiced by a famous actor.
he is voiced by tim allen
the movie even has a villian making it more interesting
Very interesting, I did not know that but it makes it sound even more interesting.
yes and even you see buzz and woody's friendship evolve from enemies to best friends
Well I will take a look into this movie and read more into it as it sounds quite interesting. Especially if it has sequels out for it.
Take care!
